body:
Well, to get rid of that same problem, we installed truffle version 3.2.1 with the following command: 
```npm install -g truffle@3.2.1```

@rfikki and @ripper234, please let me know if that version installs in windows 10 for you too. If it is so we can find out the latest truffle version that does install in win 10 and git compare with the subsequent where it doesn't install anylonger to help identifying the problem.

Hi all. These issues *should* be fixed in our latest version of Truffle, as the beta has now been pushed to production.

@bvrooman Yes, that is a breaking change. You should now use the `truffle-core` repository instead if you need that functionality. The `truffle` repository has changed to become an distribution/bundled cli package and not a development package. 

@rfikki That issue should also be fixed. Also, consider [Truffle Boxes](http://truffleframework.com/boxes/). 

If you all run into more issues, please open a new ticket and we'll address each issue individually. Thanks!
